<DocsLayout title="Estimates (Mobile)" section="Mobile App">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Create and send estimates directly from the Field Promax Plus mobile app.
    Technicians can generate estimates, add products, and get customer approval right from their phone.
  </p>
  <p>
    This streamlined process keeps things moving â€” saving time, reducing mistakes, and speeding up
    approvals so jobs don't get delayed.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>From the hamburger menu, select <strong>Estimates</strong> to view existing estimates</li>
    <li>Tap the <strong>plus button</strong> from the dashboard to create a new estimate</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Creating an Estimate</h2>

  <h3>Step 1: Start the Estimate</h3>
  <img src="/images/mobile-app/estimates_01.jpg" alt="Create Estimate" />
  <ol>
    <li>Tap <strong>Create Estimate</strong></li>
    <li>Select a <strong>customer</strong> from your list</li>
    <li>Fill in the <strong>job description</strong></li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Step 2: Add Products & Services</h3>
  <img src="/images/mobile-app/estimates_02.jpg" alt="Add Products" />
  <ol>
    <li>Select <strong>products, labor, or services</strong> needed for the estimate</li>
    <li>Specify <strong>quantity and pricing</strong> for each item</li>
    <li>Review the total before proceeding</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Step 3: Get Customer Approval</h3>
  <img src="/images/mobile-app/estimates_03.jpg" alt="Customer Approval" />
  <ol>
    <li>Present the estimate to the customer</li>
    <li>Collect the <strong>customer's signature</strong> for approval</li>
    <li>Email the <strong>PDF version</strong> of the estimate to the customer</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Estimate Workflow</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Technician creates estimate on-site</li>
    <li>Customer reviews and signs for approval</li>
    <li>Administrator is notified via email</li>
    <li>Approved estimate can be converted to a work order</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Administrators receive email notifications</strong> when an estimate is approved</li>
    <li>Technicians can create and send estimates if permissions are granted</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Ensure estimate details are accurate</strong> before sending to the customer.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Follow up with customers</strong> if an estimate is pending approval for too long.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Get signatures on-site</strong> to speed up the approval process.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
